column5: Well today, got some stuff done around the house and also found a ground blind for deer hunting that I had forgotten about    won this Propac Tent, 7 or 8 years ago when I was a member of a fishing & hunting club, had put it away somewhere in the basement and today stumble over it     It's going to be used this fall for sure  So after setting it up in the back yard, made this little video to simulate  the hunt   You must realize that in this few minutes of footage, I accelerated the process of what can be done to lure in a deer    In real mode, I only grunt 30 minutes after I'm settle in and continue to do so every 45 minutes there after.  The rattling can be used in late afternoon when deer in is the full rut and today was only able to get neighbors attention for my efforts    They thought I was nuts  Anyhoot here's the video and hope you enjoy! Nice video. Amateur porn for the hunters, very hardcore.
Are the neighbors looking at you kinda funny now Jacques

your videos make me smile all the time Jacques ...you might want to tune the call though ...first call i heard a bird...2nd call i heard a car and the 3rd call i heard a human....lol...i was actually expecting your DEAR to come walking out with a bikini on to show off her rack on the 4th call...Just kidding mon amiee ....its nice to find stuff you forgot you had ...good luck on your hunt..its obvious youll be ready for the BIG BUCK this year  Cheers! and good choice of music
Ummmmmmmmmmmmm.................I think you need to get out fishing soon.  Like real soon !!!  :w00t:  How about this afternoon??

Thanks livinisfishin!!!  Hunting porn at it's purest   Yes they are Paul    I don't know why   I sure am Sinclair   Now that was funny Dave     Thanks mon ami   I'm as ready as I'll ever be   Sorry Paul, got working on staining my wooden blind today     Maybe next time.... thanks for the offer
you got too much free time on your hands
interesting vid Jacques. I gotta say, if I was your neighbour and I was looking over the fence... ahh never mind. Enjoy prepping for the season man - look forward to the venison-in-the-pan shots.
Yeah I know   Thanks Rick!!!  venison is what it's all about for me
lol - you're really into this stuff.

Great Video,  It's ok man my neighbors think I'm nutz as well.  2 years ago I had my layout boat set up in my backyard, just like I was hunting ducks. Called and threw birds for my dog to retrieve. So I could teach her where to get in and out of the boat before moving to training on the water  LOL!

Ha....my neighbours give me the same treatment! I've already had a full spread of canadas out on the lawn, and I even test decoys in my pool LOL.  They think I'm nuts, especially when I'm hooked up to the boat in december after shoveling it out LOL  S.
Yep   Thanks RangerGuy!!!  LOL But at least you had your dog to talk to... not me   Nuts...
That's OK Jacques, you fit in just fine with all the other crazy's here.
hmm... you should try this downtown toronto and see what happens... now that would be a funny video.
